data: Foundered 2 October 1901 off Vermilion Point, along with her tow, the schooner, Michigan. Crew of both vessels were rescued by the propellers Northern Wave and Superior City with no loss of life.
Disappeared 20 October 1886 after separating from the steamer Prentice miles (km) off Vermillion Point with the loss of all 6 crew members.
Sank 6 June 1858 miles (km)above Whitefish Point and miles (km) from shore with the crew of twenty-one taking to the life boats before she sank.
Driven ashore near Vermilion Point 27 November 1872 in an arctic gale when the towline parted from steamer John A. Dix and the schooner Saturn.
Sank 10 July 1911 off Whitefish Point in a collision with William Henry Mack with the loss of three lives.
Foundered 13 May 1921 off Vermilion Point with the loss of all seven crew.
Blinded from forest fire smoke, driven ashore and stranded miles (km) east of Crisp Point Light, crew rescued by Crisp Point Life Saving Crew.
Foundered 7 Sep 1887 after breaking tow from the steamer Australasia miles (km) northwest of Whitefish Point Light, all hands, 9 lives lost.
Capsized and sank about miles (km) west of Whitefish Point. The Whitefish Point lighthouse keeper and 2 other men rescued all 11 crewmembers.
Sank 27 July 1884 in a collision with the Alberta miles (km) west-northwest of Whitefish Point with the loss of 3 lives.
Sank 26 June 1916 in a collision in a fog with the James H. Hill off Parisienne Island in Whitefish Bay with no loss of life.
Broke free and sank miles (km) south of Whitefish Point during the construction of the Harbor of Refuge in 1967.
Sank 29 July 1901 in a collision with propeller Northern Queen near Point Iroquois in Whitefish Bay with the loss of 2 lives.
Pounded to pieces 27 November 1872 after grounding just west of Whitefish Point after breaking her towline with steam John A. Dix and sister Jupiter with the loss of 7 lives.
Sank 20 August 1920 after her boilers exploded in a collision with steamer Willis L. King with the loss of 29 lives.
Sank 17 September 1873 after a collision with propeller Nipigon about miles (km) below Whitefish Point with no loss of life.

Multiplies two registers and puts the 64-bit result in two special memory spots - LO and HI. Alternatively, one could say the result of this operation is: (int HI,int LO) = (64-bit) $s * $t . See mfhi and mflo for accessing LO and HI regs.

Multiplies two registers and puts the 64-bit result in two special memory spots - LO and HI. Alternatively, one could say the result of this operation is: (int HI,int LO) = (64-bit) $s * $t . See mfhi and mflo for accessing LO and HI regs.
Divides two registers and puts the 32-bit integer result in LO and the remainder in HI.
Divides two registers and puts the 32-bit integer result in LO and the remainder in HI.
loads the word stored from: MEM[$s+C] and the following 3 bytes.
loads the halfword stored from: MEM[$s+C] and the following byte. Sign is extended to width of register.
loads the byte stored from: MEM[$s+C].
stores a word into: MEM[$s+C] and the following 3 bytes. The order of the operands is a large source of confusion.
stores the least-significant 16-bit of a register (a halfword) into: MEM[$s+C].
stores the least-significant 8-bit of a register (a byte) into: MEM[$s+C].
loads a 16-bit immediate operand into the upper 16-bits of the register specified. Maximum value of constant is 2 16 -1
Moves a value from HI to a register. Do not use a multiply or a divide instruction within two instructions of mfhi (that action is undefined because of the MIPS pipeline).
Moves a value from LO to a register. Do not use a multiply or a divide instruction within two instructions of mflo (that action is undefined because of the MIPS pipeline).
Moves a 4 byte value from Coprocessor Z Control register to a general purpose register. Sign extension.
Moves a 4 byte value from a general purpose register to a Coprocessor Z Control register. Sign extension.

shifts shamt number of bits to the right - zeros are shifted in (divides by 2^{shamt} ). Note that this instruction only works as division of a two's complement number if the value is positive.

data: Chaddi is a poor 12 years old orphan boy who earns his living by singing in trains. He lives on the streets and Rafiq Chacha, a street stall vendor acts as his guardian. Most of the time, Chaddi is harassed by the older street boys who take away most of his money. A small girl, Mili enters his life out of nowhere and changes his life forever. Chaddi takes care of her like an elder brother and sends her to school, run by a missionary. One fine day a couple turns up at the missionary and wishes to adopt Mili. Will Mili be adopted? How will Chaddi react to this? Watch this engrossing tale to find out more about the selfless nature of a young orphan living on the streets. Cast: Avhinay, Varsha, Anuj Sharma, Tarun Singh, Shrichand Makhija, Mukesh Dasmana

A couple leaves their young son, Raju, home alone on Diwali night. They are out to party and drink as they feel that it is the best way to celebrate Diwali. They leave Raju alone with their servant Ramu. Ramu too gets drunk, as it is Diwali night. Raju is drunk and scared but a thief passing by comes to his rescue. A bond of friendship develops between them. The thief, though poor, teaches the true values of Diwali to Raju. Raju's parents come back home and are shocked to find him in the company of the thief. A change overcomes the entire household and Raju's parents realize their mistake. Cast: Arif Zakaria, Virendra Singh, Roma, Sunil Jetley, Anil Sinha, Master Harsh

Rahul and Pooja are a married couple and very much in love with each other. Pooja worships Rahul and longs for him whenever he goes out of town for work. He adores children. Since the good news is delayed, both take a fertility test. Pooja gets the report, which indicates that Rahul is infertile. To save him from misery she lies to him that she is infertile. Rahuls’ attitude changes towards Pooja and eventually they get divorced. They both remarry and meet after four years in a catamaran. Rahul is the captain and ferries passengers between Mumbai and Goa. Rahul is still waiting for his wife to bear him a child. Pooja seems happy with her second marriage and Rahul is shocked when he sees her husband come to receive her with a baby in his hands. Cast: Harsh Chhaya, Irawati Karyekar, Jyotsna Karyekar

Inder is impotent. Still his mother forces him to get married to save the family honor. She gets him married to an illiterate orphan girl, Vasundhara from a distant village. She hopes that the newly wed bride will be pleasantly surprised to land up in a wealthy household and will not feel offended for being married to an impotent man. Unfortunately, when learns of his shortcomings, she rants and raves at her mother in law and Inder for having ruined her life. Young Vasundhara, loveless in life, befriends their driver Kailash, who belongs to a scheduled caste. Their friendship blossoms into love and Vasundhara becomes pregnant. When her family comes to know about it, they feel betrayed. Betrayal is not a new word for Vasundhara and she gives them a reply that makes them hang their head low in shame. Cast: Sadia Siddique, Kiran Bhargav, Tushar Dalvi, Ravi Gosai

She hopes that the newly wed bride will be pleasantly surprised to land up in a wealthy household and will not feel offended for being married to an impotent man. Unfortunately, when learns of his shortcomings, she rants and raves at her mother in law and Inder for having ruined her life. Young Vasundhara, loveless in life, befriends their driver Kailash, who belongs to a scheduled caste. Their friendship blossoms into love and Vasundhara becomes pregnant. When her family comes to know about it, they feel betrayed. Betrayal is not a new word for Vasundhara and she gives them a reply that makes them hang their head low in shame. Cast: Sadia Siddique, Kiran Bhargav, Tushar Dalvi, Ravi Gosai

Rahul is a young boy, around ten years of age, is a cancer patient. His father, Dilip is a struggling actor. His mother Mohini separated from them, as she could no longer bear his father's failures in life. Rahul and Dilip were always short of money but were happy with each other. Rahul longed for a costly music system. Dilip promised to get it for him. They both saved some money but it was spent in Rahul's treatment as he fell very ill. Dilip is not able to buy the system but Rahul still loves his father, as he is his Hero. Cast: Tejan Diwanji, Rajesh Khera, Supriya Karnik, Arun Bali, Arif Basra

This is a poignant tale about a eunuch, Ram Kali. Her family disowned her due to social pressure. She loves her younger brother but is unable to be in touch with him. She earns pretty well as the city is full of people who believe in giving alms to eunuchs to earn their blessings. She knows many influential people. She comes across Rohit, who is a disillusioned youth. Rohit had come to Mumbai with dreams of becoming a film star, but had failed. She takes over the guardianship of Rohit, guides, and helps him. He becomes a star. However, he is ashamed to let people know that he knows her and completely ignores her presence. She is heartbroken. Cast: Manish Goel, Murli Sharma, Kamal Mallik, Arun Kanan, Jasmine, Geeta Mishra, Anup Shukla, Firdaus Mewawala

Rajjat is a competent and efficient physiatrist. He plans to settle in a small town, and joins the government run mental hospital of that town. He finds the doctors working there to be too carefree and casual in nature. He comes across a patient, Bhushan, who seems well enough to be termed as a mentally sick patient. However, Bhushan refuses to step out into the real world as he finds it to be full of liars. Rajjat strikes a friendship with Bhushan and within a few days, the other doctors in the hospital realize that Rajjat too is mentally unwell. Cast: Kay Kay Menon, Atul Kumar, Meenakshi Thakur, Sushil Parasher

Rashmi is a handicapped girl who runs her own gift shop. Young Abhishek, who is working with her friend Farha, befriends her. Rashmi falls in love with him. A surprise awaits her on Valentine's Day. She is pleasantly surprised by the plans laid out by Nayanika and Abhishek for her. Cast: Harpreet Singh, Manish Goel, R.K Sharma, Radhika, Pooja, Lokesh

Kirti is a girl from a traditional family. She gets an interesting marriage proposal from a boy called Avinash. Her friend, Shikha, a girl with modern values, advises her to test Avinash before accepting the proposal. The girls lay out a plan and trap Avinash in it. The plan, however, backfires and Avinash refuses to marry Kirti. She is disappointed. She realizes that traditional values only enhance a girl's character. Cast: Akhshay Anand, Jaya Seal, Kishor Oraskar, Reena Kapoor, Kanila Dang, Subhash Sahoo, Prem Raj

Deepika and Navin are a childless couple. Deepika has had a miscarriage and is depressed ever since her doctor told her that she will never have children. Navin tries to bring her out of her depression but fails. Deepika holds herself responsible for her own misery and for Navin's, as he loves children deeply. She decides to stay away from Navin for a while and leaves for her father's house. Meanwhile, her sister Roshni is expecting and joins Deepika at their father's house. Deepika undergoes immense emotional trauma when she sees Roshni and her husband Pankaj happily share their responsibilities and worries relating to the birth of the baby. Roshni gives Deepika a gift that changes her outlook to life. Deepika finally sees light at the end of her dark tunnel. She begins to envision a happy family for herself and Navin. Cast: Shilpa Tulaskar, Vaquar Shaikh, Gautami Kapoor, Amar Talwar, Omung Kumar

Raju, an orphan girl, is a very talented dancer. A wealthy girl, she has been raised by her uncle and aunt and with great affection. When she comes of age, her uncle and aunt get her married to their son, Venkat. Raju’s marital bliss, however, is short-lived as Venkat decides to go abroad for further studies, leaving her behind. Once abroad, he shows his true colours. He writes her a letter saying that he would not be returning as he has fallen in love with another girl. What would Raju do next? How will she cope with the pain? Will she ever be happy again? Cast: Natasha Rana, Deepraj Rana, Seema Bharghav, Minal , Gargi,, Benjamin Gilani

Bhairavi is a successful career woman. She is divorced, but has a good friend in Gaurav. Mausi has been taking care of her needs since she was a child. Bhairavi has no other family members. She lives alone and is always in a foul mood. Gautam feels that she needs companionship but when he tells her that, she rebukes him. One day, Mausi brings little Anu home for a few days. Bhairavi fumes in anger as she hates children. Over the next few days, however, the little girl succeeds in changing Bhairavi's heart and mind. People around Bhairavi are pleased to see the change and finally, Bhairavi realises that life can be beautiful. Cast: Suchitra Pillai, Tanvee Hegde, Pratima Kazmi, Girish Malik

Guddu is a young man living in a big joint family. His father, uncle and brothers are all involved in the family business. They insist that he, too, join them, but Guddu has set his sight on going to Canada. Guddu has a hard time convincing his family to let him go and finally, they agree. While outwardly, they seem to be happy with Guddu's decision. However, in reality, they have agreed to let him go only because they love him too much to disappoint him. Will Guddu reconsider his decision? Cast: Mohini Mathur, R.K. Sharma, Amita, Rajneesh, Gaurav Rana, Anu Sharma, Prachi, Diksha, Joyshree Arora

Shikha and her brother have grown up to be introverts, all thanks to their authoritarian father. Ravi Malhotra, a friend of Shikha's father, thinks of Shikha as a perfect match for his son, Karan. Sanjay is on his way back home after a year when he gets stranded midway as his car breaks down. Subhash gives him a lift and drops him home. Sanjay is shocked when he learns that Rashmi, his wife, had sold the house in his absence and moved away without leaving any forwarding address. A dejected Sanjay is invited by Subhash to spend a few days in his house. Sanjay gets another shock when he sees Subhash's wife. Rashmi had married again and is now expecting Subhash's child. What happens next? Cast: Reena Wadhva, Lalit Parimoo, Sooraj Thapar, Preeti Kopikar

Vinay and Veera are going to be married in a week. They meet stealthily as they are forbidden to meet before the wedding. They go for a drive on the highway, but unfortunately, some thugs kidnap Veera. Vijay, the head of the gang, regularly supplies girls to brothels and Veera is his latest catch. Veera tries her best to escape, but is unsuccessful. Somehow, Vijay and Veera begin to get emotionally involved with each other. Will Vijay send back Veera to Vinay? or will Veera choose to stay with Vijay? Cast: Aditya Srivastava, Kartika Rane, Manish Chaudhari

Manoj, an Indian Army major, is rarely home on account of duty. His wife Shobha and his parents miss him, but are very supportive. The birth of a daughter delights him immensely. However, Runjhun refuses to accept him as a father whenever he comes home. This depresses him, but Shobha requests him to give her time to accept him. Meanwhile, Manoj is asked to report at Kargil during the battle. What will happen to the father and daughter now? Cast: Narendra Jha, Vaishnavi, Reena Kapoor, Dr. Anil Saxena, Runa Sengupta, Baby Anita, Baby Nikita, Kartik

When 70-year-old Rajan Iyer is gifted a mobile phone, he slips down memory lane. During the British era, his was one of the first households to own a telephone. Rajan, then only six years old, developed a deep bond of friendship with the telephone operator, Sweety. Rajan would often call up just to hear her sweetly ask, "Number Please". Rajan was, however, brokenhearted when Sweety just disappeared one fine day. Later, Rajan left the town only to return years later to try and locate her. Did he succeed in finding Sweety? Cast: Vinod Sharma, Mona Ambegaokar, Ravi Khanvilkar, Amar Upadhyay, Parzaan Dastur, Harshita Lal, Aditya Kapadia, Kshitij Kashyap, Bakul Thakkar, Shahnawaz

Namrata and Bunty are good friends. Both are academically bright and spend most of their time studying. Namrata's father notices that although both of them like each other, they are not at all romantic. He sees a perfect match for Namrata in Bunty and plots a way to bring them closer emotionally. Bunty, too, realizes that he is in love with Namrata, but his father opposes the wedding. Will Namrata and Bunty get married? Cast: Rita Bhaduri, Yatin Karekar, Vishwas Pandya, Eva Grover, Raju Samtani

Sania Sen is the reigning queen of Bollywood. She is a huge star with an attitude to match and is completely averse to journalists. Aditi Sharma, a young journalist, vows to find out the reason behind this. At first, Sania rebukes her but her persistence brings her closer to the star. Aditi is amazed as she gets a glimpse into Sania's lifestyle. She learns that although Sania is professionally very successful, she is unhappy in her personal life. Aditi pledges to try her best to bring cheer into Sania's life. Will she succeed? Cast: Kavita Kapoor, Candida Fernandes, Jatin Siyal, Gargi, Akhilesh Choudhari, Vallabh Chada, Jayant Bhagat

Nikhat is a well-known writer and has just published her new novel. Her ex-husband Javed finds it autobiographical in nature and comes to meet her. However, He has come at a time when there are widespread riots in town and curfew has been imposed. Nikhat begins to feel that Javed wants to patch up with her, but she is in for a surprise when his second wife defies the mob and police officers and arrives at her house. The real purpose behind Javed's visit is revealed and he leaves Nikhat's house in shame. Cast: Benjamin Gilani, Natasha Shailendra, Papia Sengupta, Tanvi

Simran is a handicapped girl and is quite pampered by her parents. She is friendless because of her rude nature. She has a pen-friend in Grace and they have been communicating regularly through letters. One day, Grace sends Tina to bring her to her house. Tina manages to convince Simran's parents to allow Simran to spend a week at Grace's house. Simran takes a dislike to Tina, as Tina appears friendlier with Grace at times. What is the reason for Simran's hatred towards Tina? How can Simran's parents allow her to go with a stranger to a pen-friend's house? Cast: Suhas Joshi, Niki Aneja, Pamela Mukherjee

Jacob and Jennifer are an NRI couple which visits India once every year. On one such visit, they happen meet 10-year-old Bunty who hails from a poor family and aims to be an armyman like his father. His father lost an arm in the war and now, runs a small tea-stall. Jennifer and Jacob fall in love with Bunty and want his parents to allow them to adopt him. Although they refuse initially, they relent when they realize that Bunty would get the best things in life if he were with Jacob in America. As his parents pack his bags, Bunty surprises them. Cast: Kishore Kadam, Minakshi Gupta, Aditi Govitrikar, Leelawar Tendulkar, Vishal

His father lost an arm in the war and now, runs a small tea-stall. Jennifer and Jacob fall in love with Bunty and want his parents to allow them to adopt him. Although they refuse initially, they relent when they realize that Bunty would get the best things in life if he were with Jacob in America. As his parents pack his bags, Bunty surprises them. Cast: Kishore Kadam, Minakshi Gupta, Aditi Govitrikar, Leelawar Tendulkar, Vishal

Jayprakash is a successful businessman, but has hardly any time for his wife and children. One day, Jay falls in love with Sunanda, a call-girl. Sunanda and Jay vibe well with each other and end up having a relationship. Jay's family is livid on learning of the affair. One day, Jay dies in an accident. His brother then dupes his family of his wealth. Jay's widow and children are ruined. At such a time, it falls upon Sunanda to come to their rescue. But she may not have a lot of time on hand. What happens next? Cast: Zarina Wahab, Kitu Gidwani, Uttkarsh Mazumdar, Rakesh Paul, Sharad Smart, Anita Thankur, Shailendra Srivastava

Sujoy and Uma have been separated for the past four years. Uma left Sujoy after she found out that he was having an affair. With great difficulty, she managed to carve a niche for herself and is now a sought-after fashion designer. Sujoy misses her and tries to woo her back. Although Uma's hurt lingers on, she still has a soft corner for him. Meanwhile, she continues to encounter hurdles in her struggle to survive as a single woman. Sujoy constantly pleads with her to come back. Will they ever be able to live as man and wife again? Cast: Natasha, Ram Kapoor, Anita Kanwal, Ragesh Asthana

Aarambh is the story of a live-in couple, Ravi and Anita. Ravi is very absent-minded and careless, and does not value relationships. Tired of Ravi's attitude, Anita is on the verge of leaving him when one day Ravi's daughter Sonia unexpectedly lands at their doorstep. The presence of his teenage daughter in the house brings about a change in Ravi. Will this change save his deteriorating relationship with Anita? Will Sonia accept Anita as her mother? Cast: Jayant Kripalani, Divya Seth, Rajeshwari Sachdev

data: The episode introduces the main characters, beginning with Melissia, Genie, and Merrill. While investigating a ruin they indicate their need for a magician to join them to open a magically sealed door. Three days later they have traveled to the town of Ohfun. Merrill and Genie individually meet Louie with mixed results. Merrill believes him to be a pervert because he was being chased by a group of angry women and that he falls, while thanking her, and pulls her shorts down. Genie meets Louie while she is being confronted by a group of their rival adventurers. They claim she has insulted them by running into one of them and not apologizing. Louie appears, impossibly wedged in a slight opening between the town wall and a building. He precedes to attack the three men using his fists. Genie sees Louie as a reckless thrill seeker. Later Melissia, Merrill, and Genie have meet up at a tavern. Merrill reveals she has learned of a pub that magicians frequent. The next night they have met up at the pub, and approach Ila. She in turn introduces them to Louie. All three refuse Louie in joining them. Ila and Louie inform them that Louie is likely the only magician willing to join them. As Louie tries to convince them of his worth he irritates Genie and she confronts him. He refuses to back down and pulls out a magical device, that he drops and damages the pub. Luckily he was the only person left in the pub as everyone else fled. Later still the three girls meet at apparently a new tavern, they are drinking and angrily discuss Louie's incompetence. Melissia then reveals she will be undergoing her "Sacred Ritual of Revealing," the next day. This is a Mylee rite that reveals a Champion to whom the priestess must serve. She envisions a dashing knight, and gets lost in her daydream of their adventures together. The next day opens on Melissia giving a sermon on Champions and heroes. She then speaks with Anna, Ganet, and Joan, three younger priestesses who believe she will be shown her champion. She calmly advises them that it may not be successful, and then when alone giggles and sings about getting her champion. The next scene shows Louie being released from jail and we find his adoptive father Master Carwes, arranged for his early release. He goes to the magician's guild and tries to attend classes but cannot get the idea of adventuring out of his mind. He and Iila talk in his dorm room, about his apparent lack of talent and dedication to his studies. As they speak about the three adventurers, they both conclude that the adventurers are looking for a magician to complete their group. Louie leaps to the conclusion that they want his help, but cannot ask him directly. He tells Ila the only member of the group he knows how to find is Melissia since she is a Mylee priestess. Genie and Merrill meet up at Genie's home outside Ohfun and their conversation turns to Louie. They decide to go see Melissia to see how her "Ritual of Revealing" has gone. Melissia is shown entering a sacred room of the Mylee temple with Chief Priestess Jenny officiating the rite. Melissia now alone and nude enters a pool of waist high water facing a statue of Mylee. To her delight, the deity speaks to her stating the next person she sees will be her champion. During the rite Louie arrives at the temple and is driven off by the three young priestesses. He then meets Genie and Merrill and after Genie pulls her sword on him, he runs away with Merrill and Genie in pursuit. As he navigates the temple he is constantly confronted by and attacked by a small army of young priestesses. He finally evades them and climbs to the top of the temple. Genie and Merrill are already there and begin to attack him. Louie pulls out his magic wand and begins to cast a spell, which backfires and destroys part of the temple roof. He falls through and lands in front of Melissia. Melissia screams, realizing Louie is her destined champion.

The girls confront Louie in Genie's home and Melissia reveals her revelation that Louie is her champion, much to her despair. Even Louie doubts the validity of this revelation. He then uses it to convince the girls to take him on their adventure. Melissia indicates she is forced to go with him if it his wish. In preparing for the adventure Louie receives a charm for his magic wand, from his adoptive father Master Carwes, and sword training from Genie. Upon leaving for the adventure Louie receives what will become a recurring task of carrying the party's equipment and provisions. Upon reaching the ruins Louie is left to move rubble from the entrance, only Genie helps out with moving the final, and largest stone. Louie then attempts to open the sealed door with his magic, but is forced to read some cheat note to complete it. Upon entering and exploring the underground ruins, the group come to a dead end room and begin to search for secret doors, Louie, by luck alone, effortlessly finds a hidden door, and envisions finding a mountain of treasure that will earn him the affections of all three girls. Instead he finds a small group of monsters called goblins. He tries to flee and rejoin the girls who were on the other side of the room. When he is struck on the back of the head he loses control of himself and begins to brawl with the goblins. While he successfully defeats them, the girls have a running dialogue of their despair at Louie not accepting his role as their magician, instead of their fighter. Louis breaks his magic wand by using it like a club. In the end they find no treasure, but Louie comments on his happiness to have been on the adventure. This provokes Merrill to punch him.

The group returns to Ohfun. The girls are still angry from not finding any treasure and uses the fact that Louie needs a wand to use magic to abandon him until he can find a replacement wand. The girls are individually shown complaining about Louie to people they know in town. They meet up an inn and Ila and Louie meet them. Ila proceeds to give Louie three useless magical items: a cloak that can make him invisible, but is too small, a box containing an illusion of a cooked chicken, and a whistle than can call demons to your location, but does not allow you to control them. When Merrill comments on how useless each one is, Ila comments that they would be more useful than non-existent teammates. This angers the three girls and Louie, perceiving their hostility, quickly excuses himself and Ila. This leads to the girls "grudgingly" helping Louie out when he decides to stock up on gear and get the wood required for his new wand. In the end, not being able to live with Louie's probable death upon entering the Phantom Forest alone hanging on their collective conscience, they decide to accompany him.

This leads to the girls "grudgingly" helping Louie out when he decides to stock up on gear and get the wood required for his new wand. In the end, not being able to live with Louie's probable death upon entering the Phantom Forest alone hanging on their collective conscience, they decide to accompany him.

The group has made their way into the forest and are finishing up a group of monsters summoned when Louie blew the whistle. After cleaning up and preparing to obtain the wood he needs, Louie notices a presence and gives chase to it, despite the girls' protests. A chase ensues, and Louie is soon captured by the presence - a female elf named Ceresia. Breaking free of his bonds, he turns the tables on her and captures her, after which the team questions her. Louie's simple nature soon finds the party prisoners in the elven village whose lands the forest is a part of. Not wanting to see what vile fate the elves have in store for them, and to show them that humans are not monsters the elves thought them to be, Louie blows the whistle, summoning more monsters, and causing the village to panic. The party takes advantage of the confusion by breaking out, and instead of running for it Louie beats the summoned monsters with a wild boar carcass and later with his fists. They bid Ceresia farewell and return to Ohfun.

One of Melissa's duties as a priestess of Mylee is to help train the young priestesses. Melissa goes to some ruins with 3 trainees to help them get experience in defeating monsters. Merill and Genie decide to come along for support and Louie, unable to resist the pull of adventure, tags along too. It turns out the ruins are infested with zombies, and once inside the floor collapses and Melissa and Louie get stuck together. They eventually find their way out, and the rest of the group leaves Louie floundering trying to find his magic wand.

Melissa's headaches double when a man shows up at the Mylee shrine professing his undying love. It's Conrad, Melissa's old fiancee. Melissa puts Louie on the spot, saying that if Conrad can beat him in a duel, she'll return to Ramliearth. If not, Conrad can never come near her again. Unfortunately, Conrad has become a master swordsman. With only a week to train, it becomes obvious that Louie is the one in danger. Melissa tries to stop the fight, but it's too late. All she can do is watch and pray.

Merill becomes so obsessed with a jar of money that she has Louie create a golem to protect it. It goes out of control, so Merill and Louie try to stop it before it throws it into a bottomless hotspring. However despite their best efforts, the jar is lost in the "bottomless" pit, and thus the group are poor once again.

The townspeople in Ohfun are busy preparing for the Mylee Appreciation Festival, which happens every five years. Meanwhile, Louie has been so engrossed in adventures, he forgot to do his homework. His instructor grounds him until it's complete. Louie works frantically to finish his tasks and barely makes it to the festival. At the festival, Melissa's three fans plot to embarrass Louie in front of her, but they end up dragging in Merrill and Genie instead. When the smoke clears, Melissa steps down and admits that Louie is her champion.

It's the middle of the summer and Louie has taken a job as a porter. Ila takes advantage of this, and while out with her on the job, he notices it begin to snow. Returning to the Guild, Ila gets a letter from Master Banarl, a magician who retired to the Tower of the Four Great Magics to complete his weather control research. He asks the group to go with her to the tower to investigate. Along the way, the group meets the elf, Celecia, who joins them. But the road won't be easy with blizzards and demented nature spirits standing in their path.

Overcoming the fierce snowstorm, the group finally arrives at the Tower of the Four Great Magics. At the entrance, they are greeted by a Flesh Golem, the gate guard resurrected by Master Banarl. Despite some difficulties, they kill the golem and make their way into the lab. There, they find the magician's frozen remains along with a horde of vicious Flau, mad ice spiritss that freeze everything they touch. The girls create a diversion as Louie heads to the main control panel. When the Flau attack, Louie makes one last gamble.

Based on information bought in a bar, Louie's group heads toward a mountain where a crystal miner named Gonga has supposedly been lost. On the way, they run into Melissa's rival, Isabel, and her team: Renard, Isabel's new champion; Jakinson, a swordsman; and Lily, a Faris priestess. When both teams find they have the same goal, the rescue turns into a race. Out of breath, the teams agree to work together. They find Gonga in a cave, but he refuses to leave without a very large crystal. With the cave ready to collapse, Louie goes in after it.

During Headmaster Carwes' absence Master Foltess takes charge of the Magician's Guild. Delighting in his new authority, he delivers a long, boring speech to a captive audience of students. After class, Louie and Ila head to the bar to meet with Louie's team. A little girl named Catherine appears, piggy bank in hand. She wants to hire them to find a "Senian Flower" for her ill grandmother. It's a rare flower not native to Ohfun. Louie finds the Guild has one in its greenhouse. He begs Master Foltess to borrow it, but he refuses. That's never stopped Louie before.

Louie and the girls meet Barb, captain of the Ohfun Royal Guard, while treasure hunting in the western reaches of the kingdom. Barb warns the group of strange activity along the border, but Genie assures him their adventure is nowhere near there. The next day, strange mercenaries attack the adventures. Genie offers to buy time for the other three so they can run to Barb's post and alert him. Melissa and Merrill go, but Louie stays, enraging Genie. Tempers flare, exploding into a fistfight between the two.

While selling flowers, Merrill is accosted by a mysterious young man. Catching her off guard, he kidnaps her and takes her to his home. He turns out to be William Wilder, heir to one of Ohfun's richest families, and he asks Merrill to marry him! Louie, Genie, and Melissa hear the good news, but something is amiss. After a little snooping, Louie finds out that William has mistaken Merrill for another girl who saved William's life in the mountains. It's up to the group to find the real girl and make sure true love really does conquer all!

Coming home from an adventure, the group runs into Ila. It seems that she had been waiting for them at her parents' lake house when she heard they would be nearby. Since the last adventure fell through, everyone decides to take a break and spend some time at the beautiful lakeside. But, when Meilssa hears of a "Guardian of the Lake" terrorizing the fishermen, she sees the perfect opportunity for Louie to prove himself. Louie, on the other hand, just wants to fish. Interests collide when Louie hooks the "Guardian" with some unique bait.

Urged by Merrill, the team heads to a ruined estate to search for treasure. There, they meet Isabel and her team. The swordsman, Jakinson, recounts some history to discredit Merrill's claim, but the two teams decide to investigate anyways, hoping to gain some adventure from the outing. They find it in spades. The adventurers fight their way through hordes of monsters to the heart of the ruin's basement, where they discover a farm for magical creatures. The ancient magic, said to be lost ages ago, is very much alive and well--and very deadly.

While visiting a small town, Louie and the others hear of a fighting tournament. It's a reunion of sorts with appearances by Conrad and Renard, for both are competing. Conrad boasts that he will win first prize as a wedding gift for Melissa. Once again, Louie is called upon to defend Melissa's honor. At the same event, Merrill overhears a plot to assassinate the tournament sponsor. She attracts the attention of the plotters, but escapes...sort of. Stuck at the bottom of a well, Merrill must find a way to send out the message before she runs out of time.

While helping Ila organize her magic item collection, Louie comes across a strange item. He plays around with it and ends up hurting himself. When Ila scolds him, Louie leaves in a huff. Ila toys with the item herself and ends up turning Louie into a woman! At first, he panics, but soon her takes advantage of this perfect opportunity and rushes into the women's sauna. But it doesn't stop there--when Melissa and Genie find Louie, he's an old man! With Ila and the item nowhere in sight, Louie's talent for embarrassing Melissa gets to shine.

One night, Merrill's shack by the river gets swept away in a flood. Disheartend, Merrill decides to buy a house with the small savings in her pot. Her despair turns to joy when she snags a house at a bargain price. The house needs some touch-ups, but Merrill is proud of her new home. Alas, misfortune strikes again as the house turns out to be haunted by an army of ghosts who have nothing better to do at night than beat each other up. With her home falling apart, Merrill enlists the aid of her friends.

Louie has been getting intensive sword training from Genie ever since he joined the team, but his skill has yet to improve. After a long training session, they go to the group's favorite bar, where Melissa tells them about the annual wine-carrying race. Seeing the chance to defeat Genie, Louie goads her into racing. On the day of the race, the three run into Conrad, who plans to use his horse in the race. Genie assures Louie that Conrad will have to ditch his horse in the rugged mountains, but the sneak knight seems suspiciously confident.

Poor Merrill. If it's not one thing, it's another. This time, she's come down with a fever. Merrill doggedly tries to return to work, but Melissa convinces her to take a sick day by offering to fill in on the job. "Job" quickly becomes "jobs" as Melissa goes through Merrill's hectic schedule of part-time professions--and gets fired from every one. In tears, she retires alone to a bar with one job left to accomplish. But Louie and Ila aren't far behind, and Melissa learns how to get by with a little help from her friends.

The hostile army gathering on the western border invades Ohfun. King Rijarl musters his own army and sets out with Headmaster Carwes and High Priestess Jenny, leaving a council of ministers in charge of the capital. In class, Ila informs Louie that the paper he asked her to translate is a list of ingredients for a powerful magical creature. But Louie has little time to ponder this mystery as he is whisked away by Master Foltess for a little work-study. There, Louie uncovers a treasonous plot--in which young Lily is playing an integral part.

After being thrown into a pit for his discovery, Louie manages to climb out and escape. With an army of mercenaries on his tail, he heads deep into the woods...only to get lost. Meanwhile, the girls have become prisoners in their own city when the regent, Lord Dardanel, declares martial law. Concerned for Louie, they begin to suspect that something is rotten in the state of Ohfun. Suddenly, the alarm is raised. When Ila confirms the cause of the alarm is Louie, the girls decide to take the law into their own hands.

After being thrown into a pit for his discovery, Louie manages to climb out and escape. With an army of mercenaries on his tail, he heads deep into the woods...only to get lost. Meanwhile, the girls have become prisoners in their own city when the regent, Lord Dardanel, declares martial law. Concerned for Louie, they begin to suspect that something is rotten in the state of Ohfun. Suddenly, the alarm is raised. When Ila confirms the cause of the alarm is Louie, the girls decide to take the law into their own hands.

Merrill, Genie, and Melissa break into the castle. Fighting their way through, Genie holds off a crowd of soldiers while Melissa and Merrill go on to confront Lily. However, the swordswoman isn't alone for long--Isabel and Jakinson come crashing through the gates to lend their support. Deep inside, Louie find an imprisoned Renard, whom he frees before continuing on his mission to give Lord Dardanel a well-deserved punch in the face. But Dardanel still has a trump card left to play. Will Louie and the girls be able to bring justice for king and country?

data: Shruti and Nikhil are a couple in love and are riding the waves of career success. They plan to get married, but decide against having children as they find it hard to look at themselves as parents. One day, Shruti is shocked to hear that her best friend Neha and her husband have been killed by terrorists. Soon, their infant baby is placed under Shruti's care and she finds it very difficult to juggle between the baby and her career. Nikhil urges her to pay more attention to her career and put the baby in an orphanage. She does so, but feels extremely guilty. Can she live with the guilt for the rest of her life? Or will she reconsider her decision? Cast: Mandira Bedi, Sanjay Singh, Amala Rai, Baby Isha Madhavi

Vishakha and Smitha are best friends. Vishaka is a bold and adventurous girl whereas Smitha is timid. They have disliked all the prospective grooms they have met until now. Once while talking on the telephone, they are connected to Anand by default. Thereafter, Anand repeatedly calls Vishakha. At first, she chides him, but later looks forward to his calls. They decide to meet in a hotel. In jest, Vishakha sends Smitha as Vishakha and Anand sends his best friend Uday to meet Vishakha. The impersonators start liking each other and both, Vishakha and Anand bemoan their ill-fated destinies. The repercussions of this joke on all four of them is worth a watch. Cast: Shammi Aunty, Sulabha Arya, Sonali Kulkarni, Shilpa Tulaskar, Darshan Jadhav, Anoop Soni, Akshay Anand

As a child, Baban was always beaten and abused by his father Suraj, for no reason at times. Frustrated, he left home at the first chance he got. He stayed at his uncle Ishwar's place and completed his education. Baban then married and lived a happy life with his wife and son, avoiding his father completely. An old Suraj pined for his son who never returned. Suraj died and left a letter for Baban. Will this letter erase all the bitter memories from Baban's mind? Cast: Mohan Joshi, Benjamin Gilani, Anup Soni, Gautami Kapoor, Miral

Pappu Pardesi is a contract killer who lives by his principles. He is approached separately by a couple engaged in a battle of sexes, a case that puts his principles at test. His ideals force him to act as mediator between the two in order to bring romance back into their lives. This act of his angers his apprentices who begin to harbour grudges against him. Will Pappu succeed in his endeavour?Will his efforts to safeguard his principles put his own life in danger? Cast: Dilip Joshi, Amit Behl, Ashwini Pande, Rajiv Kumar, Shahnawaz

Neena and Vicky fall in love and plan to get married. Soon, in an unfortunate twist of events, Vicky meets with an accident and dies on the spot. Neena's mother also becomes critically ill. A pregnant Neena is faced with a decision of either aborting the baby or marrying someone. When Neena meets Sachin through some mutual friends, she agrees to marry him. Overburdened with guilt she decides to reveal the truth to Sachin. Cast: Divya Dutta, Nakul Vaid, Samer Jaisingh, Meena Nathani, Madan Joshi, Lalit Tewari, Krishna Pal, Maya Alagh, Rohini Hattangady

While waiting for his date Paul decides to step into a music shop nearby. There, he meets Sherry and develops an instant liking for her. However, Paul is too shy to disclose his feelings to her. Sherry also likes Paul and decides to slip a note into every packet of purchases that Paul makes. These notes, however, go unnoticed. When Paul's visits to the shop become infrequent, Sherry decides to go to his home and give him a cassette that reveals her feelings. There, she learns that Paul is getting engaged the very next day. Will Paul ever know of Sherry's feelings? Cast: Jiten Lalwani, Karishma Modi, Smita Hai, Sandesh Nayak

A dejected, yet determined Shallu vows never to fall in love again and concentrate on her career. In her despondency, she lies to get the job of being a nurse to a young man, Vikas, who is suffering from Leukaemia. The day she joins, she discovers morphine injections in every room, apparently because the drug would help Vikas die a painless death. Faced with a dilemma, she decides to quit, but suddenly finds herself strangely attracted to Vikas whose tragic fate strikes a chord deep inside her soul. One day, Vikas tells her that he is fully cured and that they should celebrate. After a beach party, when Shallu retires to sleep, she finds a morphine injection lying on a chair. Cast: Pallavi Joshi, Rajesh Khera

Doraiswamy is a strict disciplinarian when it comes to his subordinates at work. He hates the lackadaisical attitude of Arun, his new peon. Every opportunity he gets to find faults and yell at Arun, he utilizes it to the fullest. Arun, however, has a hidden talent that his boss is unaware of - he is a very good singer. The office secretary likes Arun and respects his abilities. She introduces him to a band and Arun goes on to become a successful singer. How will he treat Doraiswami now? Cast: Nagesh Bhosle, Darshan Dave, Abha Dhulia, Benika, Babloo Mukherjee, Swadesh Mahaan, Raj Tolani, Gargi Nandi, Sanjay Verma, Deven Haathi

What are the parameters of judging infidelity in a friendship? Priya is a devoted wife and a loving mother who has lost herself in her mundane existence. Her children persuade her to take up job, of a trainee under Ritu, a fashion designer. What starts off as a professional relationship, soon blossoms into a beautiful friendship. One night, Ritu, in a drunken stupor, makes Priya listen to her boyfriend. Suddenly, Priya rushes back to her room. What did Priya hear? Cast: Divya Seth, Shefali Chhaya

Thakur Singh, a rich landlord, employs Karan to look after his accounts. Karan is entrusted with another peculiar task. He has to keep the Thakur's young wife amused. The Thakur is not particularly fond of his wife and is a regular visitor to Meenabai, a nautch girl. Karan develops a soft corner for the unfortunate wife, Padma. He tries his best to bring Thakur back to Padma, but fails miserably. A depressed Padma ends her life. This incident enrages Karan to such an extent that he loses the sense of right and wrong and ends up behind bars. Cast: Lalit Parimoo, Dimple Ghosh, Sajni Hanspal, Anil Sinha and Aresh

Kajal and her son Varun are happily living in their own small world. One day, Kajal’s friend introduces her to Rohit who is so awed by Kajal’s attitude that he instantly falls in love with her. He loves Varun as his own son and wants to marry Kajal. However, Varun starts feeling insecure seeing his mother and Rohit together. Kajal doesn’t want to marry Rohit at the cost of her son’s happiness. Will Rohit be able to win over Varun and Kajal? Will Varun accept Rohit? Cast: Renuka Shahane, Sudhanshu Pandey, Loveleen Mishra, Mansi Upadhyay, Parzaan Dastur

This piquant story is about Snigdha, an actress, whose career has come to unanticipated end. Faced with a desperate situation, she accepts an offer of playing the wife to DK, a rich man. When reality seeps in, Snigdha realizes that she in love with DK but her contract with him has reached its end. Will Snigdha's love remain unrequited? Does DK's contract conceal a greater truth about his life? Cast: Mona Ambegaonkar, Pawan Malhotra, Roshni, Nitin Rai, Tarun Shukla, Divya Bharadwaj

Shagun, a little boy of seven, lives with his mother Nina, an actress by profession. On weekends, he spends time with his father and his step-mother Anita, who dote on him. Shagun's performance in school drops as a busy Nina fails to give Shagun the care and love he deserves. Nina gets into the wrong circle of friends and Shagun resents their gatherings at his house. He hatches a plan and lies to the local police that his mother is in the company of drug users. The police arrive at the scene and arrest Nina and her friends. Shagun is remorseful, as he wanted the police to take away his mother's friends and not her. Shagun has to go and live with his father and awaits his mother's release. Will Nina forgive Shagun for lying? Will their equation with each other change? Cast: Yash Pathak, Nivedita Bhattacharya, Harsh Chhaya

Old is gold. That is what Sonu realized after he made new friends. Sonu, Gaurav and Puneet were very close and good friends until Jazz came along. Jazz a.k.a. Jasmeet was a crafty fellow who used friends to his benefit. Sonu, being naive, was incapable of noticing this. Under the influence of Jazz and his cronies, Sonu courted trouble at school and at home too. He ignored his old friends and they felt hurt. Once Sonu got into trouble just before his school exams and Jazz refused to help him out. Sonu longed for the company of Gaurav and Puneets. Will Sonu garner enough courage to call them? Will they forgive Sonu and help him out? Cast: Sudha Chandran, Abhinay Patekar, Rahul Dhanvani, Nayan Joshi, Vishal Thakker, Manmohan, Eklavya, Joy Sengupta

The management of an old age home has been on the look out for a caretaker for a long time, but it seems that hardly anyone wants to take the opportunity to pamper the egos and the bickerings of the senile inmates. The warden is on the verge of a breakdown when Vidhant, a young man, enters their lives as the caretaker. The old age home transforms from being a place where dejected people dump their dreams into a place where they start aiming to touch newer horizons. However, it is time for Vidhant to leave and no one can stop him. No one can defy the laws of nature, can he? Cast: Paintal, Rajeev Verma, Subbiraj, Sulabha Arya, Vinay Jain, Jacqueline Julian, Chandan. S. Tyagi, Archana Joshi

Rajan and Suman have been married for five years and are very much in love with each other. However, their family members are concerned as they are childless. One night, while returning from an outing, a ruffian rapes Suman while Rajan remains helpless in saving her. They do not reveal the incident to anyone. Later, Rajan seeks Suman's forgiveness for not being able to help her. As things turn out, Suman gets pregnant soon and delivers a baby boy. Rajan hates the child, Sumit, but his parents and Suman adore him. Suman pleads with Rajan to give the child his love, but Rajan is adamant. Years later, Rajan happens to bump into the ruffian once again. What the thug reveals that day changes Rajan's equation with his son forever. Cast: Juhi Parmar, Prithvi Zutshi, Aabha Parmar, Master Sumit, Saptarishi Ghosh http://www.rajshri.com/Video/Rishtey-Naata

Rahul constantly tells Nisha to concentrate less on her career and give more time to their infant daughter Pinky. This often leads to arguments and one day, a tired Nisha leaves Pinky and Rahul. A few years later, Nisha wishes to bring Pinky back into her life. She manages to get a court order that instructs Rahul and his second wife Asha to return Pinky to her biological mother. Pinky and Asha are shattered beyond words as they both adore each other. Will Nisha be able to carve out a niche for herself in her daughter's life? Will Asha be able to overcome her grief? Cast: Achint Kaur, Vaquar, Anita Kulkarni, Madan Joshi, Baby Lekhni

Is it a mere coincidence that Vikram resembles Sameer in so many ways? Cast: R. Madhavan, Mouli Ganguly, Nandita Thakur, Sunil Sodhi, Jaya Bhattacharya, Master Yashraj Kushwaha

Shastri is a typical Hindi teacher who detests English being spoken in his class. Tanuja is a teacher of English, who wears short skirts. Both Shastri and Tanuja can't stand the sight of each other and the poor students have to bear the brunt of their mutual hostility. When Shastri suddenly realizes that Tanuja has been absent from school for several days, he pays her a visit. Finding an ailing Tanuja, he nurses her back to health - a fact that astounds the entire school staff. Call it love or curiosity, one day, Shastri gets a tip about Tanuja going to meet her lover in a secret place. Piqued at this, he decides to go there himself. What surprise awaits Shastri? Discover the magic of ‘east meets west’ in this delectable episode of 'Rishtey'. Cast: Rajit Kapur, Kitu Gidwani, Jogi, Seeta Ram, Achyut Potdar

Sagar, a struggling writer, and Kamal, an aspiring actress, have to share the same flat as roommates - a fact that is hard to digest for both of them. One day, Sagar rescues Kamal from an unfortunate situation and Kamal finds herself opening up to Sagar. While Sagar strives to make a living for himself, he is always a pillar of support for Kamal, consistently helping her spread her wings far and wide. An inherent realization that enshrouds these dreamers is the fact that when dreams become real they always come with a price. Cast: Sagar Arya, Anwesha Bhattacharya

A story of undying hope and ever-cherished desires, 'Umeed' revolves around Sudarshana. Living in a quaint mountain-village, she marries her childhood sweetheart Rakesh. Being a constant pillar of support for her husband, she allows him to follow his dreams of becoming a soldier. While Rakesh fights for the country, Sudarshana weaves a sweater for him, something that becomes a symbol for all her dreams, desires and hopes. As her wait gets prolonged, she learns that she is pregnant. Will Sudarshana’s wait ever come to an end? Cast: Vani Tripathi, Bobby Poonia, Shashi Sahay

Will you comfort an AIDS victim? This message-oriented episode of 'Rishtey' is about Karan and Nikki, whose beautiful world is shattered when Karan is diagnosed with AIDS. Suspecting her husband of infidelity, Nikki leaves him. Away from Karan, she starts working as a counselor for an NGO, an experience that acquaints her with AIDS victims. But will this experience be strong enough for her to return to Karan and come to terms with reality? Cast: Rameshwari, Sudhanshu Pandey, Meenakshi Gupta, Dev Joshan, Savy Sidhu, Neelofer Khan, Sanjay Aggarwal, Master Sanjay, Meghna Khanna

Seema is a career-minded single mom and Abhinav, an inexorable ad-man single-dad. Having been let down in the past, Seema has almost given up on men, except for her son. The only thing that Seema and Abhinav have in common are identical cellular phones, which get switched when both are going through a hectic day. They least expect to get attracted towards each other. But the next thing they know, they're falling in love. Cast: Parmeet Sethi, Shefali Chhaya, Bimal Oberoi, Dev Trivedi, Miral, Bhakti Kulkarni

On the eve of their twenty-fifth wedding anniversary, Rajiv and Nandini decide to part ways to follow their long-lost love interests. They decide to meet each other after a period of six months to finalize their divorce. But both of them inevitably realize that their forlorn love interests have kept their respective pasts behind them and have moved on with the flow of time. Cast: Shishir Sharma, Smita Jayakar, Anil Dhawan, Neelima Azeem, Jayati Bhatia, Dharam Taneja

Rahul Singh, a struggling actor, meets Divya Dalal at a discotheque one night. Divya, who is double Rahul's age, develops a liking towards him. Their relationship soon blossoms into love and Rahul starts living with Divya. On Divya’s recommendation, he soon gets break as the lead actor in a film. When Rahul travels outdoor for shooting, he meets a young Sapna, a film journalist, and they fall in love. Rahul tells Divya about this and shows her Sapna’s photo. Divya is shocked to see the photo. What happens next? Cast: Moonmoon Sen, Rohit Sehgal, Shruti Ulfat

This is the story of Hansa - a wife and a doting mother. Gautam her husband is a workaholic and her son Rahul constantly yearns for his company. Gautam is a loving father and husband but is unable to devote time to his family due to work pressures. Hansa comes across Adi a bachelor in one of her frequent solo outings with Rahul. Rahul and Adi bond well as friends but both adults develop a soft corner for each other. One day Hansa decides to disclose all to Gautam and plans to leave her family for Adi. Twenty years to this decision she reminiscences on her judgment. Watch this segment to see how she feels. Cast: Sushma Prakash, Arjun Raina, Denzel Smith, Kanwar Katar

Adi, a widowed father, decides to bring up his children Pinky and Babloo singlehandedly. He refuses all offers to remarry. A few years later, Adi meets Shraddha, a girl far younger to him, and falls in love with her. They decide to marry but now, Adi's grown-up children refuse to accept her. Shraddha patiently tries to woo the children, but fails miserably. The children are livid with her for encroaching their space and freedom and plan to leave home forever. It is either them or her in their 'mother's house'. Cast: Raju Kher, Mandira Bedi, Prachi Singh, Moolraj Rajda, Jay Devi, Rohit

Shweta finds a diary in her late grandmother Priya's room and is intrigued by it. In the diary, her grandmother has mentioned a dear friend named Vikram who seems to have made a big difference to her life in just a few moments. She has also talked about a home called 'Priyashiana'. Shweta sets out on a journey to know the unknown and comes across a man who calls himself Kapil uncle. Who is Kapil uncle? How does he know everything about Priya? Cast: Pawan Malhotra, Mrinal Kulkarni, Charmee Shah, Yash Tonk

In the diary, her grandmother has mentioned a dear friend named Vikram who seems to have made a big difference to her life in just a few moments. She has also talked about a home called 'Priyashiana'. Shweta sets out on a journey to know the unknown and comes across a man who calls himself Kapil uncle. Who is Kapil uncle? How does he know everything about Priya? Cast: Pawan Malhotra, Mrinal Kulkarni, Charmee Shah, Yash Tonk

Sujata's husband Ashish is completing his doctoral thesis abroad. Sujata lives alone, waiting for the moment when her husband will return. She longs to meet him, talk to him and be with him. She confides her feelings in her neighbor Sandy. Suddenly one day, Ashish arrives and Sujata's joy knows no bounds. However, her happiness is short-lived. Within a couple of days, she realizes that Ashish is a changed man. He just does not have time for her. This upsets her and she walks out of the house. Will Ashish try to locate her? Will Sujata rethink her decision? Cast: Harsh Chhaya, Nivedita Bhattacharya, Yatin Karyekar

Rahul is a blind boy in his early twenties and lives a closeted life with his mother in a peaceful locality. She has never allowed him to grow up. His mother has always treated him like a small boy and expected him to respond like one. Rahul's life takes an about turn when Bindiya comes to live in the adjoining flat. Friendship blossoms between the two, much to the chagrin of his mother. All the emotions Rahul had withheld in him so far explode like a volcano. An insecure mother lashes out at Bindiya and forbids both from seeing each other. Will Rahul gather enough courage to follow the right path? Will his mother realize that she is smothering her son with her love? Cast: Surekha Sikri, Joy Sengupta, Nivedita Bhattacharya, Goolshan Masdiani

The main protagonists of this love story are Akanksha and Vineet. Akanksha, a businesswoman and a frequent visitor to Matheran, meets Vineet who is blind and lives at the hill-station. Having similar interests in life brings them closer and they fall in love. Akanksha forces Vineet to get operated in Mumbai and his vision is restored. His joy is transitory as he starts suffering from blackouts. A visit to the doctor erases all his dreams of a new life with Akanksha. He returns to Matheran without informing her. What made him act this way? How will Akanksha deal with his loss? Cast: Mandira Bedi, Rohit Roy, Shailendra Singh, Payal, Umesh Bajpai

Anu, a fiercely independent ad maker, thinks of commitment as an imprisonment. Hence, she shirks from settling down with Rishabh who is also an ad man. While pondering over her purpose in life, Anu comes across Ghanti, a foul-mouthed street urchin who would rather sell flowers stolen from a cemetery than beg. Anu starts nurturing the thought of adopting Ghanti. Will Anu be able to bring about changes in Ghanti’s life? How will Rishabh react to her decision? Cast: Karan Trivedi, Divya Seth, Jayant Kripalani, Luvleen Mishra

With the tendency of human beings to trivialize relationships when they exist, we fail to realize their importance in our lives. On his deathbed a father’s only wish is to see his son. This wish encapsulates his incessant wait to reach out to his son, to bridge the gap in their relationship. Will there be an end to his wait? Cast: Ravindra Mankani, Vinod Shekhavat, Zahida, Dhruv Khandelwal, Rishabh Khandelwal, Vishal Thakkar

Vinny lives alone with her mother who is a workaholic and is quite averse of dogs. Often seeking a companion, Vinny is very happy when her best friend Meghna goes for a vacation, leaving her pet dog with Vinny - a fact that Vinny hides from her mother. Will Vinny’s mother ever discover her secret? What will be the repercussions? A treat for all animal lovers, this episode of 'Rishtey' makes a delectable watch. Cast: Prajakti Deshmukh, Pooja Kanwal, Neelu Kohli, Amrita Prakash, Geeta Nair

Years after achieving independence, we find India in the throes of corruption, nepotism and red-tapism. Suffering the consequences of holding on to his ethics and morals is a freedom fighter, and his devoted wife. While his children blame him for their inefficiency, his grandson considers him to be his Ideal. Addressed as a ‘morally selfish’ man by his sons, he is trapped between his ideals and what his sons consider to be his 'parental-responsibility'. Cast: Navin Nischol, Uttara Baokar, Uday Nene, Lalit Parimoo, Narendra Gupta, Naresh Suri, Aman Verma, Moon Moon, Poonam Jha, Pratibha Sharma

Cast: Pawan Malhotra, Shruti Ulfat, Abha Dhulia

On New Year's Eve, Joy meets Jyoti and falls in love with her. Two more chance meetings and he decides to marry her. But both Joy and Jyoti are engaged albeit to different individuals. Sandeep, Jyoti’s fiancé, is enraged and threatens Joy. Suddenly, Joy disappears. Will this love culminate in marriage? Is it strong enough to withstand the obstacles? Cast: Sangeeta Ghosh, Joy Sengupta, Anang Desai, Shama Deshpandey, Prithvi Zutshi, Rohit Sahgal, Madhu Malti, Manju Vyas

Hussain, a disillusioned Kashmiri, runs away from his home town of Kashmir and lands in Mumbai. He has lost every member of his family to the terrorists. He settles himself as a watchman in a housing society named 'Shanti Nivas'. The name of the society is quite contradictory to the real atmosphere prevailing in the society. The warring neighbours do not get along well and Hussain has to bear the brunt of their hostilities most of the time. He tries to bridge the gap between the neighbours, but his efforts turn futile. There is utter chaos and confusion in the society most of the time. An untimely catastrophe strikes the residents and they are stunned. How long can rivalry prolong in the face of the trials and tribulations that befall them? Cast: Suresh Chatwal, Shashi Sahai, Dolly Bindra, Murali Sharma, Mukesh Ahuja, Hansa Singh

This episode of 'Rishtey' features a story about love and inhibitions in a society ridden with superstitions. Based on a Saratchandra classic, 'Vachan' is the story of a child-widow, whose very presence is considered to be inauspicious, and her lover, who is willing to shun the society, and even his own desires to get her love. Cast: Manasi Joshi Roy, Jatin Sial, Jaya Bhattacharya

A heart-rending story ensues when an honest police officer and a convict, who has killed for his ideals, meet. The interaction with the convict leads the cop to start questioning his honesty and he ultimately allows the convict to escape. Why does a man who has spent years cherishing his honesty and his untarnished career, willing to let go of his reputation? Is fate relentless? What does it have in store for both of them since each one has actually done what he thought to be right? Cast: Vikram Gokhale, Sunil Sinha, Jehangir Khan, Sunil Shende, Phalguni Parikh, Madhuri Sanjeev, Sweta Gautam, Prashant, Sanjeev Choudhary

A young photographer, Rohan comes to live in a new neighborhood. He finds himself attracted to a very beautiful girl in the opposite building. He befriends a kid, Carey from her building assuming him to be her brother. Carey tells him that he is his parents' only child and the house where he has seen the beautiful girl is haunted. The servant and neighbors warn him against looking in the direction of the girl's house. Sometimes she sends him love letters professing her love for him and on other days, she ignores him. After days of exasperation, he finally comes face to face with the spooky girl. Was Carey right? Is Rohan in love with a ghost? Cast: Rohit Bakshi, Radhika Menon, Lovleen Mishra

data: Second World war Bomb disposal hero Captain 'mad Hoagy' Hoagland, now fallen on hard times, appears at Brighton Police Station to deliver two boxes. One contains a silver truncheon; an award for valour for Sergeant Brunswick. The other contains the head of one of Mrs Groynes' old criminal accomplices Birthmark Potter. It is a warning to them all that Mrs G's criminal nemesis Adelaide Vine is heading back to Brighton, and that the sadistic criminal Terence Chambers is heading for town too; both hell bent on havoc and revenge.

It is a warning to them all that Mrs G's criminal nemesis Adelaide Vine is heading back to Brighton, and that the sadistic criminal Terence Chambers is heading for town too; both hell bent on havoc and revenge.

Captain 'mad Hoagy' Hoagland reassures a doubtful Sergeant Brunswick that he does indeed deserve his silver truncheon award for bravery, and saves the day at the bandstand presentation ceremony of this presentation when he defuses a ticking bomb in a box with the aid of his old army bomb disposal team member Terence Chambers, who discovers that criminal Adelaide Vine has arranged for the severed head of his old criminal fraternity friend Birthmark Potter to be placed in the ticking box so it will appear that Mrs Groynes is responsible for his murder. Vine is led off by Chambers to meet her fate at his hands, and the Brighton police station team learn that Inspector Steine can be persuaded into all kinds of useful behaviour by the employment of reverse psychology...

There's a talent contest at the Hippodrome, and Mrs G and Sergeant Brunswick take part in it and win with a new song. Inspector Steine has written and delivered a landmark broadcast on the topical legal case known to the newspapers as 'Tatiana and the Five Hats', and Fred Nesbit a Canadian film maker, and his English assistant Leslie, come to Brighton to make a film about the work of the Brighton police force. But Mrs G uncovers Leslie's plan to plot to show the police in a terrible light ; revealing that he is in fact that most dreaded and feared of 1950s creatures; a Commie! It's becoming clear Mrs G is deeply smitten by Captain Hoagland, and also that Adelaide Vine is still alive, well and plotting further dastardly events to torment the Brighton police force, and Mrs G herself.

data: The original Dungeons & Dragons was published in 1974 as a boxed set containing three separate booklets: Volume 1: Men & Magic Volume 2: Monsters & Treasure Volume 3: Underworld & Wilderness Adventures This original version of D&D only included a few of the elements considered core to modern D&D and required the player to own several other games in order to make full use of the rules, however it is considered the first of what we now consider role-playing games and, along with its supplements, is responsible for the creation of the genre itself.

data: Izaaz works in Dubai and comes to India for Id. While buying present for his mother he sees a beautiful girl and falls in love with her. His mother takes him to a family to fix his marriage. Here Izaaz meets the same girl, whom he had seen earlier in the shop. However, she is not the girl whom he has come to see. Izaaz's marriage is fixed with another girl in the same house and he finds himself in a dilemma. Cast: Tejasvini Kolhapure, Vaquar Sheikh, Tuhina Vohra

Love indeed conquers all superstitions. Sadanand is one such person who is trapped in the belief that number 7 is lucky for him. In order to break this obsession his friends make him meet Suparna who lies that she was born on 07/07/77. They fall in love and later it is revealed that she has no association with the number 7. However, their immense love easily overlooks this superstition. Cast: Rituraj, Gracy Singh, Ashish Roy, Ravee Gupta

Moira lies to Ranbir, her husband about meeting her Aunt Leela on weekends but meets her lover, Rohan. Rohan wants to marry her but she is not interested. Rohan gives her a necklace as a parting gift, which mesmerizes her. However, she mortgages the necklace to avoid getting into trouble with Ranbir. Then she pretends her aunt has died and left some mortgaged jewelry for her. Next day forcibly, Ranbir goes to collect the necklace. However, a shock awaits her when Ranbir gives her a gold pendant and his secretary, Nikki the necklace. Out of humiliation and helplessness, Moira kills Ranbir. Cast: Masood Akhtar, Irawati Harshe, Arif Zakaria, Dipen Vartak

Simi is forced to stay at her in-laws house when her husband, Deepak is away for sometime. Her father-in-law does not like her modern lifestyle. The generation gap between Simi and her father-in-law cause arguments between them. Meanwhile Simi in her own way is able to win everyone’s heart. Slowly the hatred in her father-in-law’s heart starts dissolving as he realizes her care and love for him. However, Deepak and Simi have to leave the house as Deepak gets a job elsewhere. The father-in-law confesses his feelings to Simi. Cast: Bashir, Nandita Thakur, Archana Bhardwaj, Master Shyam

This episode talks about the relationship between a mother and a son. Roy Fernandez is a lively teenager who like most other teens wants freedom to live life his way. However, a loving Julia Fernandez is always overprotective about him. Roy misunderstands this as interference until he realizes the true worth of his mother. Cast: Vishal Malhotra, Preeti Dayal, Reo Kapadia, Kanika Shivpuri, Radhika Menon, Nilesh, Aditi Gulati, Dinesh Khanna, Amit

Since the death of his beloved wife an old man has become irritable and lonely. On the advice of their psychiatrist friend, his son and daughter- in- law employ Savitri , an old woman as a house keeper. Savitri fills up the void in the life of this old man who eventually falls in love with her. But the problem is will he be able to express his love to her? Cast: Satyen Kappa, Sulbha Arya, Raahul Mahiyaria, Mahroo Sheikh, Varun Vardhan

Pinaki Ranjan Ghosh an unemployed youth passes his time playing carom board with his friends. He also keeps giving wrong guidance to his neighborhood boy Mohit. One-day Mohit’s father gives Pinaki the responsibility of teaching Mohit. However, Pinaki and Mohit together have fun instead of studying. Mohit’s father not knowing what is happening thanks Pinaki for taking Mohit’s responsibility. This touches Pinaki and he changes overnight, due to which he has a fight with Mohit. Pinaki stops meeting Mohit. In the following days, Mohit passes his exams and Pinaki comes first in the civil service exams. Both congratulate each other and make up. Cast: Joy Sengupta, Omkar Kapoor, Sunil Jaitley, Hemant Choudhary, Lalitesh, Sweta Rastogi, Beenu Kalsi

Amar is a novel writer who writes biographies of convicts who are given death sentence. He releases his new book, which is a biography about Marthand who is sentenced to death. Amar meets Pareen a beautiful girl who has been sentenced to death for murdering her mother. Initially Pareen is silent, however a couple of meetings later she opens up. In the course of their meetings, Amar falls in love with Pareen and decides to marry her. Amar applies for Amnesty on behalf of Pareen. The government rejects the application and Pareen is sentenced to death. Unable to bare the pain Amar commits suicide. Cast: Renuka Shahane, Krishnakant Sinha, Mandeep Bhander, Rajesh Khera, Pratima Kazmi

Amar meets Pareen a beautiful girl who has been sentenced to death for murdering her mother. Initially Pareen is silent, however a couple of meetings later she opens up. In the course of their meetings, Amar falls in love with Pareen and decides to marry her. Amar applies for Amnesty on behalf of Pareen. The government rejects the application and Pareen is sentenced to death. Unable to bare the pain Amar commits suicide. Cast: Renuka Shahane, Krishnakant Sinha, Mandeep Bhander, Rajesh Khera, Pratima Kazmi

This episode is a humorous look about life after marriage. Revathy and Vinod, a separated couple, coincidentally find themselves working in the same office. During this period, both remember their past days as a couple. Both are amusingly surprised to realize that they still love each other immensely and divorce is not a solution to any marital problem. It requires an understanding on both ends to make a marriage work. Cast: Pawan Malhotra, Renuka Shahane, Achut Potdar, Bharti Achrekar, Abhay Bhargava, Ajay Wadavkar, Raj Tilak, Ajit Mehra

Anjali and Raj get divorced. Rachna and Sooraj, their kids suffer silently. Raj remarries. Shikha is a wonderful step mom to the kids. Anjali cannot bear this and tries to instigate the children against Shikha. The kids however side with Shikha especially when Sooraj gets lost for a while due to his own carelessness. Anjali finally realizes her folly. She understands that she was self-centered. Her conscience asks her to leave them in peace so that she can retain the remaining bond she has with the children and her old house. Cast: Sudhir Mitoo, Vani Tripathi, Mandeep, Richa Madhusudan, Gurdas Singh

Sanjay falls in love with Shirley. Her brother, Mario tries to tell Sanjay about Shirley's illness, but Sanjay brushes him off. Shirley is terminally sick with cancer. One day Sanjay proposes but Shirley evades the topic and starts talking about Death. He is very irritated and angry with her for changing the subject from love to death. He leaves the house unable to understand her behavior. He later regrets his actions but it is too late as Shirley is dead by the time he goes back to her. He visits the lakeside where they both used to meet and reminiscences about her and feels happy. Cast: Ankush Mohla, Sandhali Sinha, Ajay Gehl

Mahajan and his wife are a middle aged couple who live in their sprawling ancestral house. They are childless. Mahajan is retired and they have ample time between them. They are constantly fighting and arguing about trivial issues. A young couple with their little daughter Nayana, who needs temporary accommodation, comes into their life for a short period. They hold the young couple and Nayana close to their heart only to realize that people have grown very selfish in the materialistic world. Cast: Sukanya Kulkarni, Sanjay Mone, Lovleen Mishra, Rajesh Tandon, Hemu Adhikari, Amba Patki

Clara D'Souza is a young mother living alone and supporting her young daughter Sharon single handedly. Her husband had left both of them when Sharon was only two years old. No one befriends Sharon, as she is poor. She plans a birthday party for her friends but no one turns up. Sharon is very depressed but smiles when her grandmother gifts her a teddy bear locket. The bear is supposed to have magical powers. Sharon's life changes drastically after she wears the Teddy Bear locket. All her wishes are fulfilled. Cast: Sucheta Parose, Baby Sana Shaikh, Anant Mahadevan, Anita Kanwal

Neha and Shekhar's parents fix up their matrimonial alliance. But both have different principles about the perfect spouse. Their wavelength does not match. However they become friends while expressing their likes and dislikes to each other. Neha's problem is that if she does not find a suitable groom for herself she will have to marry Shekhar. She entrusts the help of Shekhar to reach her goal. Shekhar enthusiastically fixes her up with a few alliances but it is too late, as Neha has fallen in love with Shekhar. Cast: Seema Shetty, Rohit Sehgal, Deepak Vartak, Amit Behl

Rohit is a drug addict. His parents have left him at Manav's drug rehabilitation centre.Rohit befriends an orphan Mohit, and both manage to procure drugs by unfair means to satisfy their cravings. Tanya, a girl who lives near the centre comes to the centre for an exhibition. She chides Rohit for being an addict. Rohit takes her rebuke as a challenge and resolves to kick his habit. He and Mohit both kick off their addiction. Rohits parents come to take him home. He also takes his young friend Mohit along with him. Cast: Benjamin Gilani, Usha Nadkarni, Tushar Dalvi, Kshiti, Harshad, Nimish

Chanda loses her soldier husband in the war. Captain Chachi consoles Chanda and tells her to be brave and carry on life positively. Even though Chachi is dressed as a married woman, she reveals that she too is a widow. She reveals that she lost her husband years ago in the freedom struggle. Chachi says that when a soldier loses his life for the country, the wife changes from being a 'suhagan' to a 'sada suhagan'. People around her are not happy with the change she wants to bring in their traditional values. She plans to leave the society for good when they stop her and accept her and her ideals. Cast: Himani Shivpuri, Rajnibala Sharma, Jaya Mathur, Randeep Singh, Neha Pandse, Abnar, Jeet Atal, Sunil Jetley, Yash Shah, Savu Siddhu, Vijay Sinha

Balu is a mentally challenged man in his forties. His old mother looks after him on her paltry pension. She has not received pension for the last two months. She finds it hard to cook one fair meal a day. She has few well-wishers who help her occasionally. She is worried about Balu. Who will take care of him if she dies? One day as she is returning with food she meets with an accident. Balu is left at home alone and unaware of his mother's death. Cast: Meenakshi Thakur, Vrajesh Hirjee, Mithilesh Chaturvedi, Aslam Farshori, Sai Sabakar

Kavita and her Boss Samaar are locked up in the office one night. Next day morning is Samaar’s wedding. Samaar is a very rigid and strict man, while Kavita, his secretary is a fun loving girl. For Suraj his seven-year-old son Ayush is his world, and it is the same for Ayush too. After his wife’s death, Suraj has been the mother, father, friend and guardian to Ayush. On Ayush’s birthday, Suraj gifts him a bike, Ayush goes out on the bike, meets with an accident, and dies. Suraj is shattered. Isha arrives in his life. Though he is unable to forget his wife and son, Isha is able to bring happiness into his life. Isha delivers a child and they name him Ayush. One night, Isha leaves the house,the child and a letter in which she reveals that she had driven the car that had killed Ayush. Suraj is shocked! Cast: Sudhanshu Pandey, Sucheta Paushe, Raj Tolani, Lata Acharya, Master Vinnie

Neera a successful professional wants to have a child without marriage. She makes an agreement with an unemployed youth Sagar Khanna for Rs. 50,000/-. They decide that they will go to a hill station for a few days so that nobody comes to know who the father of the child is. Neera gets pregnant and the agreement gets over, and both start living their own lives, but fate has something else in store. One day, Sagar meets Neera with her child, and he realizes what it means to be a father after seeing the child. Sagar’s love for the child finally unites him with Neera. Cast: Asif Shaikh, Nevedita Bhattacharya, Eva Grover

Vikram Saluja a flirt visits a restaurant with one of his girl friends, Sapna. In the restaurant, he sees an extraordinarily beautiful girl, Anamika, and falls in love with her. . Gradually, a friendship develops between them and results in love. Vikram meets Anamika’s parents and their marriage is finalised. Suddenly Vikram is back in the restaurant with Sapna and realizes that all that was a dream. He gets up, approaches the girl sitting opposite him, and gets the shock of his life. What is the truth behind the beautiful face? Cast: Joy Sengupta, Tony Mirrchandani, Amrita Saluja, Eva Grover

Arjun, an ambitious youth, wants to use his creative talents and become an Ad. Filmmaker, while his father wants him to take up a job and settle down. This is where the differences start. The clash between two generations reaches a crescendo, and one day Arjun leaves his house. The cold war continues until the day Arjun’s wife gives birth to a child. On his father’s friend’s request, and his wife’s insistence, Arjun calls his father and talks to him. Finally, father and son unite. Cast: Vikas Anand, Anoop Soni, Sonam Malhotra, Arun Bali, Meenakshi Verma

Five retired friends get together and spend their time playing cards. They enjoy their retired life to the hilt. One day suddenly one of them dies. Fear and depression grips all the friends. They stop meeting. Once they recover from the shock, they start meeting again. Soon one more friend dies. Once again, gloom descends on the friends. Finally, the remaining three friends realize that life must go on. A touching tale on friendship that also brings out the truths of life and death. Cast: Parikshit Sahani, Virendra Saxena, Arun Bali, Sushil Parashar, Ajit Mehra, Yashodhan Bal

One scary night Reema Pradhan is raped by three teenage boys. That incident keeps haunting her for years, even a change of city and a new job as a PRO does not eradicate the pain and trauma of that incident from her mind. Then one day her Boss Rahul proposes marriage, her father accepts the proposal. Reema is reluctant. Reema decides to reveal the truth to Rahul. Will Rahul accept her after knowing her past? Watch “Ittefaq”. Cast: Akshay Anand, Anita Kulkkarni, Rajendra Gupta

general term that refers to a horse which has white or dark spots over all or a portion of its body.
